&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harbor&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Application Consultant Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our dynamic Enterprise Solutions – Financial Systems team. Our team is at the forefront of innovation and delivery for our law firm clients, with deep experience in evaluating law firm financial system technology, developing technology and process roadmaps, system selection and implementation, and change management. We work with leading vendors allowing clients to benefit from our product-specific expertise and market perspective. We serve both as advisors and as experienced, scalable hands-on resources, collaborating with our clients to implement operational improvement, efficient data management, and technology usage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a part of the Financial Systems Team, we will rely on you to work closely with Harbor project team members and clients to lead requirements gathering and analysis, executing against legal technology best practices, and leveraging our methodologies to facilitate the selection, implementation and/or optimization of legal technology systems and tools leveraged by our clients. As a Manager you will provide line management and mentoring support to junior consultants within the Financial Systems team to ensure that they are following good practice in terms of client interactions both from a technical and consulting perspective. You will have a responsibility towards ensuring billable utilization of your team is at consistently expected levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Job Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage industry knowledge, organizational skills, and project experience to support all aspects of finance projects including facilitating requirements gathering, preparing documentation of processes, and helping to implement identified solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide specialist knowledge of the given technical applications (e.g., Elite 3E, Aderant Expert) in terms of good practice and knowledge transfer to the client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and develop technologies based on technical requirements and design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support client business process review, identify key client business requirements and support transformation of business requirements to technical requirements and design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft deliverables during a project lifecycle including findings and recommendations, functional and technical design documents, data maps, test scripts, training and communication plans, training guides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide line management and mentorship to Junior Associate Consultants to build knowledge both from a technical and a consulting perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in business development efforts such as proposals (RFPs), workplans, and presentations by collaborating with team members and leaders across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct research on client industries, legal technology, and legal industry trends to identify Finance Operational system and process opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the evaluation of new products and services that have been identified as opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation and maintenance of Financial System “pitch” collateral to make sure they remain relevant and available within the practice group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become proficient in specific legal technologies related to active projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seek opportunities to proactively contribute to the growth and development of the Finance Systems team and Harbor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently maintain ~80% of time spent on client-billable projects for both you and at 80% for your team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Experience, Education and Other Qualifications:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in legal technology contributing to assessments, requirements gathering, system design, configuration, implementation, testing and deploym

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Harbor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt; is seeking &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Applications Support Analysts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt; to join our dynamic Legal Technology &amp;amp; Operations –&amp;nbsp;Applications Management Services&amp;nbsp;team. Our team is at the forefront of delivery&amp;nbsp;of a quality service&amp;nbsp;for our clients&amp;nbsp;who have managed service agreements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We have both extensive&amp;nbsp;experience in legal processes and technology&amp;nbsp;across several platforms.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This&amp;nbsp;mainly focusses&amp;nbsp;on&amp;nbsp;Intapp, Elite 3E and&amp;nbsp;iManage&amp;nbsp;products but also includes others where integration is essential, e.g. practice management systems, document management&amp;nbsp;systems&amp;nbsp;and external data providers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We serve both as advisors and as experienced, hands-on resources, collaborating with our clients to&amp;nbsp;contain&amp;nbsp;risk and cost through operational improvement, efficient data management, and technology usage.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335557856&amp;quot;:16777215,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;As an analyst, you will be expected to collaborate with senior and junior-level internal resources, as well as clients, to ensure correct prioritization and timely delivery of both a “business as usual” type model for our clients as well as some “continual improvement” tasks.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;This is a position that will be hybrid with an office in the metro Manila area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 2&quot;&gt;Job Duties and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 2&quot;&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245418&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134245529&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:120,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The role is split into 2&amp;nbsp;main areas&amp;nbsp;of responsibility:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Monitoring and resolving issues within client production environments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This is termed “business as usual”.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:120,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Improving configuration and processes for&amp;nbsp;clients,&amp;nbsp;based on changing needs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This is termed as “continual&amp;nbsp;improvement”.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:120,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Business as usual includes the following responsibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;u

&lt;p&gt;As a Consultant at &lt;strong&gt;Harbor&lt;/strong&gt;, you will engage with colleagues who are smart, innovative, and eager to meet new challenges. An entrepreneurial spirit and positive “can-do” attitude are the common threads that unites us to drive forward and succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Associate Consultant&lt;/strong&gt; is an early-career professional who demonstrates the ability to contribute independently to client projects while continuing to build depth in technical and consulting expertise. Consultants are expected to balance strong client-service skills with growing technical proficiency, managing multiple deliverables in dynamic, fast-paced environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At this level, Consultants move beyond foundational execution by taking ownership of discrete workstreams, applying problem-solving skills to moderately complex challenges, and contributing to process improvements. They are relied upon to communicate effectively with technical and business stakeholders, maintain a high billable utilization rate, and adapt quickly to new technologies or shifting client needs. This role represents the transition from a support-focused contributor to an independent consultant who consistently delivers value while continuing to learn under the guidance of senior colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical concepts clearly and effectively in both verbal and written formats with technical staff, business users, and management personnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple deliverables in a fast-paced environment, adapting to shifting priorities while maintaining quality and timeliness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong working relationships with colleagues and clients through advanced interpersonal skills and professional client service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply strong analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills to resolve moderately complex technical and functional challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quickly adopt new skills and adjust to challenging priorities, technologies, and client requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and improvement of applications or integrations within defined frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognize recurring or moderately complex issues and contribute to the development of effective solutions with guidance from senior consultants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend improvements to tools, processes, or designs based on project experience and client feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support knowledge sharing by documenting lessons learned, contributing to process documentation, and assisting junior team members when possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of focused client-facing workstreams or deliverables, ensuring completion on time and to a high standard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively provide updates to project leads and clients regarding task status, risks, or potential roadblocks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve in a primarily client-facing capacity, participating on camera for client meetings and engaging in occasional in-person client interactions as requested.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in solution design discussions, offering input based on practical project experience and emerging technical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate professionalism, accountability, attention to detail, and sound time management when managing client and internal deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have permanent US work authorization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to remote applicants in US and Canada. Strong preference for Chicago-based applicants who can work up to 2-3 days per week from the Chicago office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Computer Science, Economics, Marketing, or Accounting preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of one year of relevant work experi

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harbor&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant, ELM (Enterprise Legal Management) - Project Lead&lt;/strong&gt; to join our dynamic Corporate Legal Technology team. This role is ideal for a highly experienced legal technology consultant who has successfully led complex legal technology initiatives from assessment and requirements gathering through design, configuration, testing, deployment, change management, and optimization. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our team is at the forefront of innovation and delivery for our corporate legal department clients, with deep experience in evaluating legal processes and technology, developing technology roadmaps, system selection and implementation, and change management. We work with leading vendors allowing clients to benefit from our product-specific expertise and market perspective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt; In this role, you will serve as a client-facing project lead and trusted advisor, partnering with corporate legal department clients to evaluate processes, define requirements, design practical technology solutions, and guide implementations that improve operational efficiency, data management, risk mitigation, and cost control.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;As a member of the Corporate Legal Technology Team, you will manage projects and clients, leading requirements gathering and analysis. You will execute legal technology best practices and utilize our methodologies to facilitate the selection, implementation, and optimization of legal technology systems and tools for our corporate law department clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt; The successful candidate will be expected to lead workstreams, guide junior and senior team members, manage client expectations, and drive complex legal technology initiatives from discovery through deployment. This is a full-time, remote position that can be worked from anywhere in the US, with preference being given to candidates who can work Hybrid from our Chicago headquarters.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
